</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=ebullition>Ebullition</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/7/02 5:16:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2051.topic&index=37>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: hmm</span><hr size=1> Yeah, great, Hamstring does more damage, but I can NO longer use it.  That is wonderful.  Quickness was changed so I now attack slower than before, too slow to use my styles.<br>
<br>
Okay, this new patch caused a ton of problems for me.<br>
<br>
I am Level 48 and have a LOT of quickness, and I use a sword with 4 delay.<br>
<br>
Mainly this part:<br>
<br>
- In our buff system overhaul of last version, we introduced a bug that we must take steps to fix. The effect of Quickness buffs increased overall player damage per second far more than same-level strength and dexterity buffs (thus removing the need to have strength and dexterity buffs in some cases). So, we've reduced the effectiveness of quickness buffs by 10-15% (depending on the level of the spell). This change will affect all melee and archer characters who have Quickness buffs cast on them. You will notice that you attack a little slower now than you used to when your Quickness is buffed. <br>
<br>
- We found that Combat Haste buffs are far too effective - they lower player's attack timers down to 1.5 seconds or less, in some cases. Their effectiveness has been reduced, and it now abides by the overall 1.5 second attack timer clamp. This change affects melee character who had Combat Haste buffs cast on them (although not archers, who were not affected by Combat Haste buffs). Please note that we have lessened the effect this change has on Friars by bumping up the effectiveness of their self-haste buff to compensate. <br>
<br>
<br>
This changed a LOT more than just spells. As a kobold melee rogue I get a lot of quickness. I am now attacking a LOT slower than before.<br>
<br>
I am now attacking slower than before. I NEVER had buffs before, I don't have them now. I simply attack slower than I used to. I am using the EXACT same equipment that I was using last night, but now I attack slower and do the same damage as always.<br>
<br>
<br>
And I am not out of sync with a lot of creatures and I can NOT use Hamstring EVER after I use my Perf chain because I attack to slow to get the move in before the next attack. The only way I can do it is to press Hamstring BEFORE I get the attack text of the creature and hope I get an Evade.<br>
<br>
Before Patch I would go<br>
<br>
Perf<br>
Monster hits me<br>
Creeping Death (stuns monster)<br>
Stunning Stab<br>
Hamstring<br>
Monster attacks again<br>
<br>
Now it goes<br>
<br>
Perf<br>
Monster attacks<br>
Creeping Death (stuns monster)<br>
Stunning Stab<br>
Monster attacks<br>
My next attack<br>
<br>
BUT I am doing the exact same damage as before. So Quickness now LOWERS my damage but does NOT speed my attack.<br>
<br>
I have NO self buffs and NO magical buffs. <br>
<br>
I simply now attack much slower, so slow that I can't use Hamstring anymore because the timing is so slow that I can NOT react in time anymore.<br>
<br>
Quinkness SUCKS. It lowers our damage cap, it lowers our over all damage from styles, and it NO longer speeds up my attacks.<br>
<br>
I got nerfed. The patch says this was to change BUFFS cast on me, but I don't have any BUFFS cast on me.<br>
<br>
This is a HUGE problem for my Shadowblade. Basically I lost an attack and I lost the ability to use my Evade style.<br>
<br>
